  "abstract": "The discovery of stable genetic male-sterility in pigeonpea (Cajanus cajan (L.) Millspaugh) and its non- additive\r\ngenetic variation for yield has paved the way for breeding hybrids. Male-sterile genes have been transferred\r\nto promising cultivars to develop male-sterile lines. ICPH 8 the first hybrid pigeonpea was released in 1991.\r\nThis bulletin describes the advances made in hybrid pigeonpea research and the factors involved in the\r\ncommercial exploitation of hybrid seed production.",
